         <entryFree xml:id="k000281" type="architectural feature">
            <term xml:id="term-k000281-1" xml:lang="zh-latn-pinyin-nt">chaji</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000281-2" xml:lang="zh-Hant">岔脊</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000281-3" xml:lang="zh-Hans">岔脊</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000281-4" xml:lang="zh-latn-pinyin">chàjǐ</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000281-5" xml:lang="zh-latn-wadegile">ch`a-chi</term>
            <term xml:id="term-k000281-6" xml:lang="en" type="literal_translation">branching ridge (lit.)</term>
            <idno type="URI">https://architecturasinica.org/keyword/k000281</idno>
            <note type="Note">
               <p>under construction</p>
               <p xml:lan="en">Literally “branching ridge,” chaji refers to the corner ridges of a building with a hip-gable (<term ref="/keyword/k000143">xieshan 歇山</term>) roof.</p>
               <p xml:lan="en">The term chaji was first documented in the Qing dynasty （Yongli 2000, 446） and is synonymous with the term “bracing ridge” (<term ref="/keyword/k000280">qiangji 戧脊</term>). Although Liang Sicheng 
                  preferred to use qiangji exclusively in his Qingshi yingzao zeli 清式營造則例（Liang 1981, 37),  both terms remain in use among contemporary scholars when discussing the corner 
                  ridges in a building with a hip and gable (xieshan 歇山) roof.</p>
               <p xml:lan="en">Some modern scholars have expanded the use of chaji to include two additional architectural features: the section in front of the tile animals on the roof 
                  ridge (traditionally called shouqian 獸前) （Lv and Liu 1992,111）, and the corner ridges of the lower roofs in multi-story buildings (traditionally called <term ref="/keyword/k000279">jiaoji 角脊</term>) （Qi 1999,270）.</p>
               <p xml:lang="zh-Hant">“岔脊”指中國古代建築歇山屋面轉角之脊。“岔脊”一詞最早出現於清代文獻，與戧脊同意。(《工程做法则例》（胤礼 2000,446） )梁思成曾經棄用岔脊，僅以戧脊指歇山屋面轉角之脊（梁 1981,37），
                  但當代學者仍同時使用岔脊和戧脊指代歇山屋面轉角之脊。（王 1996,203）此外，也有部分學者將垂脊中垂獸之前的部分（吕和刘 1992,111），或重簷建築下層簷的簷角屋脊稱為岔脊（齐 1999,270）。但在古代文獻中前者
                  稱為“獸前”，後者為角脊。</p>       
            </note>
